@alexander-akait You're right - I've moved the runtime requirements to `ModuleChunkLoadingPlugin` where they belong. 1391884f513bd8d8085257fdee0279e80a426bd5
These requirements are needed because the ESM HMR update handler uses `publicPath` to construct the import URL and `getChunkUpdateScriptFilename` to determine the update chunk filename. I noticed `JsonpChunkLoadingPlugin` follows the same pattern in its `hmrDownloadUpdateHandlers` hook.

Moved them from `HotModuleReplacementPlugin` to keep the separation clean - HMR plugin handles the update flow, chunk loading plugin handles how chunks are loaded.

